In [4]:
treatment_contrast = Treatment(reference = 'B').code_without_intercept([ 'B','A'])
lm_smf_res = smf.ols (formula="income ~ C(group,treatment_contrast)+ jobexp +\
                C(group,treatment_contrast):jobexp" , \
                data = df).fit()
#Group A
dfA = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['jobexp', 'group'])
dfA['jobexp'] = np.arange(1, 21.5, 0.5)
dfA['group'] = 'A'
Ay_fitted = lm_smf_res.predict(dfA)
#Group B
dfB = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['jobexp', 'group'])
dfB['jobexp'] = np.arange(1, 21.5, 0.5)
dfB['group'] = 'B'
By_fitted = lm_smf_res.predict(dfB)
#plt
#Fitted and observed
df_A = df[df.group == 'A']
df_B = df[df.group == 'B']
plt.figure(figsize=(7, 6))
plt.scatter(df_A.jobexp, df_A.income, facecolors = 'red')
plt.plot(dfA.jobexp, Ay_fitted, 'r.', markersize = 4)
plt.scatter(df_B.jobexp, df_B.income, facecolors = 'blue') 
plt.plot(dfB.jobexp, By_fitted, 'b.', markersize = 4) 
#approriate axis labels and pegends
plt.xlabel('jobexp')
plt.ylabel('income')
plt.ylim(0,50)
plt.legend(['A (observation)','A (prediction)','B (observation)','B (prediction)'],loc='upper left')

plt.title('LM: Rsquared = 0.29') #title
plt.show()
#R^2 = 0.292
lm_smf_res.summary()

treatment_contrast = Treatment(reference = 'B').code_without_intercept([ 'B','A'])
lm_smf_res_plus = smf.ols (formula="income ~ C(group,treatment_contrast)+ educ + jobexp +\
                C(group,treatment_contrast):jobexp" , \
                data = df).fit()
#Group A
dfAp = pd.DataFrame(columns = [ 'educ', 'jobexp', 'group'])
dfAp ['educ'] = [18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18]
dfAp['jobexp'] = np.arange(1, 21.5, 0.5)
dfAp['group'] = 'A'
Ay_fittedp = lm_smf_res_plus.predict(dfAp)
#Group B
dfBp = pd.DataFrame(columns = [ 'educ', 'jobexp', 'group'])
dfBp ['educ'] = [18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18,18]
dfBp['jobexp'] = np.arange(1, 21.5, 0.5)
dfBp['group'] = 'B'
By_fittedp = lm_smf_res_plus.predict(dfBp)
#plt
#Fitted and observed
df_A = df[df.group == 'A']
df_B = df[df.group == 'B']
plt.figure(figsize=(7, 6))
plt.scatter(df_A.jobexp, df_A.income, facecolors = 'red')
plt.plot(dfAp.jobexp, Ay_fittedp, 'r.', markersize = 4)
plt.scatter(df_B.jobexp, df_B.income, facecolors = 'blue') 
plt.plot(dfBp.jobexp, By_fittedp, 'b.', markersize = 4) 
#approriate axis labels and pegends
plt.xlabel('jobexp')
plt.ylabel('income')
plt.ylim(0,50)
plt.legend(['A (observation)','A (prediction)','B (observation)','B (prediction)'],loc='upper left')
plt.title('LM: Rsquared = 0.83') #title, much better, compared with without edcu, wow! 
plt.show()
#R^2 = 0.830
lm_smf_res_plus.summary()

df1 = pd.get_dummies(df)  #dummies
df2 = df1.iloc[0: , [0,2,3]] #group B as reference
X = df2[['jobexp','group_A']].values #X 
Y = df2.income.values #Y
#R^2 = 0.37
fitcriterion = 'squared_error' #'squared_error', “friedman_mse”, “absolute_error”, “poisson”
tree = DecisionTreeRegressor(criterion = fitcriterion, max_depth = 2,max_leaf_nodes = None).fit(X, Y )
tree.tree_.node_count #number of terminal nodes
tree.tree_.max_depth
tree.score(X, Y)
plot_tree(tree)

*Part C - K Nearest Neigbors -- Without eduction --------- Midterm 7*¶

In [14]:
df1 = pd.get_dummies(df) 
df2 = df1.iloc[0: , [0,2,3]] #group B as reference 
df3 = df2.iloc[0:, [1,2]]
#standardize training set
df3_sta = (df3 - np.mean(df3))/np.std(df3,ddof = 1) 
X = df3_sta[['jobexp','group_A']].values #X 
Y = df2.income.values #Y
#fit knn with k = 12
knn_res = KNeighborsRegressor(12).fit(X, Y)
#standardize test set
df3_joxexp = np.arange(1, 21.5, 0.5)
df3_jobexpsta = (df3_joxexp - np.mean(df3.jobexp))/np.std(df3.jobexp,ddof = 1) 
#Group A
dfA = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['jobexp', 'group_A'])
dfA['jobexp'] = df3_jobexpsta
dfA['group_A'] = '1.997999'
Ay_fitted = knn_res.predict(dfA)
#Group B
dfB = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['jobexp', 'group_A'])
dfB['jobexp'] = df3_jobexpsta
dfB['group_A'] = '-0.499500' #Group B
By_fitted = knn_res.predict(dfB)
